<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <para>With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore of the housing
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302580">Figure 80</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install O-ring in the tower
                groove.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302580" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302580" filename="../figg13/G1302580.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Install Spade Pin in Bore of Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot
                    and install the tension spring washer over the ball, dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302581">Figure 81</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302581" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302581" filename="../figg13/G1302581.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Install Tension Spring Washer Over Ball</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing, seating one coil at a time (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302582">Figure 82</hotlnk>). Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302582" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302582" filename="../figg13/G1302582.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 82. Install Tension Spring Under Lugs in Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302583">Figure 83</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302583" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302583" filename="../figg13/G1302583.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 83. Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
